  "prompt": "What makes mayonnaise a dairy product?",
  "response": "Mayonnaise is actually not considered a dairy product. While it is sometimes mistaken for being in the dairy category, mayonnaise is traditionally made from ingredients such as oil, egg yolks, vinegar or lemon juice, and seasonings. Dairy products are typically made from milk, such as cheese, butter, yogurt, and cream. Since mayonnaise does not contain milk or milk-derived ingredients, it is not classified as a dairy product.",
